pe":"Feature","geometry":{"coordinates":[[-121.73023999999998,45.394716,0],[-121.72974299999998,45.393683,0],[-121.72858400000001,45.39278,0],[-121.728137,45.39199,0],[-121.72828300000003,45.391332,0],[-121.72789499999999,45.390383,0],[-121.728813,45.389996,0],[-121.72707300000002,45.389723,0],[-121.72568899999999,45.388316,0],[-121.72470299999998,45.386815,0],[-121.72456353190205,45.38656300955846,0]],"type":"LineString"}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"name":"Cerberous Moulin"},"geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-121.71795845031738,45.38494834654316,0]]}},{"properties":{"name":"McNeil Shelter"},"type":"Feature","geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-121.73197567462921,45.39550807123145,0]]}},{"geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[[-121.78586393594742,45.40759301195957,0]]},"properties":{"name":"Parking"},"type":"Feature"},{"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-121.724374294281,45.386229331594656,0]],"type":"Point"},"properties":{"name":"Entrance?"},"type":"Feature"},{"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-121.77736401557922,45.40173448319876,0]],"type":"Point"},"type":"Feature","properties":{"name":"Reference Picture"}}]},"description":"<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><p>Oct 2019 - These caves may no longer exist.\n<\/p><p>Amazing mile long Ice Caves on the North West side of Mt Hood. \n<\/p><p>Ice caves can be EXTREMELY dangerous, especially during periods of snowmelt. If you decide to go, it is better to visit them in Fall or Early Winter. During Late Winter they will get covered by snow and access trails or even roads may be impassable.\n<\/p><p>Mt Hood weather can be a problem when accesing the caves, make sure to check in advance:\n<\/p>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http:\/\/www.mthood.info\/mt-hood-weather.html\">http:\/\/www.mthood.info\/mt-hood-weather.html<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http:\/\/www.nwac.us\/avalanche-forecast\/current\/mt-hood\/\">http:\/\/www.nwac.us\/avalanche-forecast\/current\/mt-hood\/<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n<meta property=\"mw:PageProp\/toc\" \/>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Approach\">Approach<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Hike up to McNeil Point Shelter and from there do the exposed off-trail traverse to the entrance of the caves, you should be able to see the cave entrances from afar. The traverse may require ice ax and crampons, make sure you are prepared for it. \n<\/p><p>Google Earth view of the route, original reference picture can be seen <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/photos3.meetupstatic.com\/photos\/event\/8\/4\/7\/8\/highres_299493912.jpeg\">here<\/a>.\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r1062633282\">@media all and (max-width:720px){.mw-parser-output .content .thumb>div:not(.thumbinner){display:flex;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;align-content:flex-start;flex-direction:column}}body.skin-vector .mw-parser-output div.thumb>div:not(.thumbinner){font-size:94%;text-align:center;overflow:hidden;min-width:100px}body.skin-minerva .mw-parser-output div.thumb>div:not(.thumbinner){margin:0 auto;max-width:100%!important}<\/style> \n<\/p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div style=\"display:table;\">\n<span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:Error mw:File\/Frameless\">\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Descent\">Descent<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>There are three caves: Snow Dragon, Frozen Minotaur and Pure Imagination. Maps available from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/ohdgrotto.caves.org\/snow-dragon\">OHD Grotto<\/a>. Experienced cavers may also consider rappeling down the Cerberous Moulin and do a through trip of Snow Dragon.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Exit\">Exit<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Retrace your steps back to the car.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Red_tape\">Red tape<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Beta_sites\">Beta sites<\/h2><\/div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/wyeastblog.org\/2013\/09\/29\/sandy-glacier-caves-realm-of-the-snow-dragon\/\">WyEast Blog<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/www.outdoorproject.com\/adventures\/mountaineering\/mount-hood-sandy-glacier-ice-caves\">Outdoor Project<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/www.portlandhikers.org\/forum\/viewtopic.php?f=8&amp;t=17391\">Porland Hikers<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media<\/h2><\/div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/www.opb.org\/glaciercaves\/\">OPB Documentary (Article)<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/watch.opb.org\/video\/2365095891\/\">OPB Documentary (Video)<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=E55Qw27Urys&amp;feature=player_embedded\">Video Rappeling Snow Dragon<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/www.meetup.com\/Portland-Hiking-Group\/events\/10818508\/\">Portland Hiking Group Meetup<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/www.meetup.com\/NW-Wilderness\/events\/146813762\/\">NW Wilderness Meetup<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Background\">Background<\/h2><\/div>\n\n\n<\/div>","technicalRating":2,"vehicle":null,"name":"Sandy Glacier Caves (Snow Dragon)","shuttleSeconds":null,"riskRating":"R","rappelCountMin":null,"rappelLongestMeters":null,"latitude":45.4075,"rappelCountMax":null,"longitude":-121.7858,"waterRating":"A","id":6160,"timeRating":"IV","months":["Jul","Aug","Sep"],"version":"ac1e593007bba7999fa82d4b20f52492c6ca8cf95f00232ff89cd9d75052fab6","url":"https:\/\/ropewiki.com\/Sandy_Glacier_Caves_(Snow_Dragon)","permit":"No","quality":4}